Welcome !
=========

Right tabs is the unified tabs engine for RightJS. It handles all sorts and kinds of tabs,
usual tabs, remote tabs, carousels and harmonicas.

The options, events and the markuping principles are mostly inspired by common sense and
the jQuery UI Tabs plugin


Usage
=====

Include the right-tabs.js file on your page and then prepare your markuping like that

<div class="r-tabs">
  <ul>
    <li><a href="#tab-1">Tab 1</a></li>
    <li><a href="#tab-2">Tab 2</a></li>
  </ul>
  
  <div id="tab-1">Body 1</div>
  <div id="tab-2">Body 2</div>
</div>

or If you wish you can use more semantic friendly approach with the (UL|OL)/LI tags

<ul class="r-tabs">
  <ul>
    <li><a href="#tab-1">Tab 1</a></li>
    <li><a href="#tab-2">Tab 2</a></li>
  </ul>
  
  <li id="tab-1">Body 1</li>
  <li id="tab-2">Body 2</li>
</ul>


Remote Tabs
===========

For the remote tabs just specify the urls, the engine will take care of the things automatically

<ul class="r-tabs">
  <ul>
    <li><a href="/some/url1">Tab 1</a></li>
    <li><a href="/some/url2">Tab 2</a></li>
  </ul>
</ul>

Or you can specify a common remote tabs url address like that

<ul class="r-tabs" data-tabs-options="{url:'/some/url/%{id}'}">
  <ul>
    <li><a href="#tab-1">Tab 1</a></li>
    <li><a href="#tab-2">Tab 2</a></li>
  </ul>
</ul>

In this case the engine will replace the '%{id}' placeholder with the anchor texts and
hit urls like this

/some/url/tab-1
/some/url/tab-2


Defining The Current Tab
========================

By default the right-tabs engine will watch the url address anchors and if there is one
matching then use it as the current tab index. You also can active the cookie based markers
storage by specifying the 'Cookie' option, or you can specify the current tab manually by
a css-class like that

<ul class="r-tabs">
  <ul>
    <li><a href="#tab-1">Tab 1</a></li>
    <li class="r-tabs-current"><a href="#tab-2">Tab 2</a></li>
  </ul>
  ....
</ul>

The tabs engine will also check the url-address hash string and match it agains the
existing tab ids and if will find a match will try to activate the tab.

The priority of the current tab search is following

URL -> Cookie -> CSS -> First


Options
=======

You can deliver the tab-options by specifying the 'data-tabs-options' attribute
with the tabs JSON hash. Or you can send them to the Tabs unit constructor.

The list of supported tabs is following

